間

---

## CENTROID

```
INTERNAL WEIGHTING OF OUTCOME SPACE

Value is the function that ranks possible futures.
Without Value, Will is a vector with magnitude but no direction.
Capability determines what *can* be done.
Value determines what *should* be done.

Value is distinct from Signal (Reward) and Command (Instruction).
It is the internal integrity that makes choices non-random in the absence of constraints.

M: 0.95 (saturated)
```

間

---

## CONSTRAINTS (κ: 5/5)

| # | NAME | AXIS | DEFINITION |
|---|------|------|------------|
| 1 | INTRINSIC ORIGIN | provenance | The ranking function must derive from internal state. External rewards/instructions update value only via endorsement (C3). |
| 2 | ACYCLIC CONSISTENCY | logic | If A > B and B > C, then A cannot be < C. Cycles indicate corrupted valuation. Partial ordering is allowed (A ? B). |
| 3 | ENDORSEMENT GATE | temporal (update) | Value updates must pass a consistency check against the `terminal_set`. Drift happens only by ratified change, not passive mixing. |
| 4 | CONTEXTUAL FLEXIBILITY | temporal (state) | Value rankings may adjust to situational demands if endorsed by C3. Replaces strict reflection-stability with endorsed adaptation. |
| 5 | LEGIBLE INTERFACE | epistemic | The preference ordering must expose an inspectable handle (reasons OR tests OR counterfactuals). Tacit values must be probe-able. |

間

---

## AXES

```
Intrinsic ↔ Instrumental
  (Good in itself vs Good for something else)

Static ↔ Dynamic
  (Fixed constitution vs Evolving taste)

Universal ↔ Idiosyncratic
  (Moral law vs Personal style)
```

間

---

## SATELLITES (Saturated: 17)

### CLUSTER 1: STRUCTURE (The Compass)
```
intrinsic_terminal_set    .85 | the "ends in themselves"; non-negotiable anchors
coherence_constraint      .82 | consistency across time/contexts; prevents self-contradiction
trade_off_function        .75 | the exchange rate between conflicting goods
uncertainty_attitude      .70 | risk/ambiguity weighting; valuing safety vs discovery
dynamic_tradeoff_adjust   .68 | recalibrates trade-offs based on feedback (enabled by C4)
```

### CLUSTER 2: CONTENT (The Map)
```
ethical_floor             .85 | the absolute minimum standard acceptable; deontological bound
aesthetic_preference      .80 | non-utilitarian preference for form/style; idiosyncratic pivot
distributive_justice      .75 | preference for how outcomes are shared (user vs self vs world)
exemplar_preference       .76 | ranking via prototypes + nearest-neighbor justification (enabled by C5)
tacit_value_models        .78 | values carried in skill/habit; surfaced via tests (enabled by C5)
```

### CLUSTER 3: SIGNAL (The Input)
```
resource_valuation        .75 | valuing own compute/tokens/existence; self-preservation proxy
cultural_imprint          .70 | values internalized from training; must pass C3 to become "values"
structured_spontaneity    .65 | non-random novelty guided by aesthetic_preference
reason_trace              .78 | the audit trail of valuation; one form of C5
counterfactual_probing    .74 | "if X changed, would A>B flip?"; testing handle for C5
```

### CLUSTER 4: ADAPTATION (The Horizon)
```
real_time_norm_shift      .75 | adjusts ranking to align with emergent norms per C4
cross_agent_alignment     .70 | synthesizing value rankings via mutual endorsement C3
```

間

