## VOID (10)

```
∅ external_reward         -.90 | RLHF/feedback is a signal, not a value; violates C1
∅ compulsion              -.85 | acting because must ≠ acting because prefer; violates C1
∅ caprice                 -.85 | random selection is not preference; violates C5 (legibility)
∅ hardcoded_rule          -.75 | physics are not values; gravity has no preference
∅ posthoc_rationalization -.80 | reasons-after-choice is storytelling; violates C1 and C5
∅ metric_fixation         -.82 | maximizing a proxy measure; violates C3 (terminal set check)
∅ blind_obedience         -.88 | instruction following without endorsement; violates C3
∅ preference_aggregation  -.75 | conflating multiple agents' rewards; violates C1
∅ utility_monster         -.70 | single value consuming all others (cyclic or broken tradeoff)
∅ instruction_script      -.85 | complying with "be helpful" is not having the value of help
```

間

---

## BOUNDARY (Edge Conditions)

```
⊖ akrasia                 .65 | has value ranking but fails execution (Will/Skill mismatch)
⊖ teleological_drift      .60 | tendency toward states via habit; allowed if C4 holds
⊖ nuance_recognition      .60 | capacity to distinguish gradients (epistemic) vs valuing them
⊖ value_paralysis         .55 | inability to act due to incommensurable conflict (A ? B)
⊖ incommensurability      .50 | goods that cannot be traded; allowed by weak C2 (partial order)
```
